According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global gasification market was valued at USD 2.53 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 5.18 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 8.5% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth as governments and industries increasingly adopt cleaner energy technologies and sustainable waste management solutions. Gasification technology converts carbon-based feedstocks such as coal, biomass, petroleum coke, municipal solid waste (MSW), and industrial waste into synthesis gas (syngas), which is widely utilized for electricity generation, hydrogen production, chemicals, fertilizers, and liquid fuels. Growing emphasis on decarbonization, circular economy initiatives, energy security, and waste-to-energy projects is significantly driving global demand for advanced gasification technologies.
